INSERT INTO `blog_posts` VALUES (42,'Raghu-Engineering-College','Raghu Engineering College (Autonomous) is an engineering college located in the outskirts of the city of Visakhapatnam, Andhra Pradesh, India. Established in 2001, it is situated on NH-43, 37 km away from Visakhapatnam and 15 km away from Vizianagaram. It is an AICTE, New Delhi approved engineering institution and is affiliated to Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University - Gurajada, Vizianagaram. The chairman is Kalidindi Raghu an academician.[1]\r\n\r\nThe college is located in the suburbs of Dakamarri Village of Bheemunipatnam mandal in Visakhapatnam District. The 40-acre (160,000 m2) campus of Raghu Engineering College is home to the infrastructure, faculty and support facilities. While providing an on-campus residence for students, the college has its own transport facility from Visakhapatnam, Vizianagaram and Bheemunipatnam for the day scholars.\r\n\r\nFacilities include a library, computer labs for various purposes, separate CAM and CAD labs program guided machine operations and sports complex.\r\n\r\nRaghu Engineering College Raghu institution of technology and Raghu college of pharmacy are situated in a same area and popularly called Raghu Educational institutions. The all over students are more than 7000+. ','img/raghu.jpg','Jitendra Choudary','2023-11-03 12:19:47'),(44,'Incredible-India','India is the seventh-largest country by its geographical area and is located in South Asia. The beauty surrounds our country from each and every aspect. India is also known by two other names Bharat and Hindustan and the people of India are known as Indians. The national anthem of our country is “Jan Gan Man” and the national song of our country is “Sare Jahan Se Achcha”.\r\n\r\nIndia is a Democratic country where people themselves choose their leader and live with freedom i.e. they can do anything they wish to within the limits of the law. If any citizen of India tries to harm any other person, there are also rules and regulations to punish him in order to make him realize his mistake.\r\n\r\nOur country is also incredible because of its beautiful mountains, lakes, forests, seas, oceans, etc. Many foreigners each year visit India to see the beauty of our country that is its rich historical temples, its traditions, its language, its heritage, etc.\r\n\r\nDifferent Regions of India\r\nNorth Region\r\nNorth Region consists of the most incredible thing in the world that is The Himalayas which is the highest mountain in the world. This region also consists of the beautiful Kashmir covered with mountains. It consists of Uttar Pradesh which is mainly known as the land of Krishna, land of Rama, etc. This region also consists of one of the wonders of the world i.e. Taj Mahal which people come to visit across the world.\r\n\r\nSouthern Region\r\nThis is the “Land of Nawabs”. It is famous for its festivals, food, and languages. The place is famous for its rice dishes. This region consists of cities like Kerala, Tamil Nadu, and Karnataka, etc.\r\n\r\nEast Region\r\nEast part of  India consists of West Bengal, Jharkhand, Bihar, Odisha,  etc. The capital of West Bengal, Kolkata is the largest city of this section and is the metropolitan city and is the third’s largest city in the country. Kolkata is known for its sweetness and festival.\r\n\r\nWest Region\r\nThe West part of the country is really incredible as it is covered with sands and deserts. Rajasthan, Gujarat, and Maharashtra are the three most amazing places in this region. The culture, the language, the traditions and the clothes of this region are incredible and you will love to visit this region.\r\n\r\nIndian Culture and Religion\r\nIndia’s culture is among the world’s oldest; civilization in India began about 4,500 years ago. India has 29 states with different culture and civilizations and one of the most populated countries in the world. The Indian culture, often labeled as a mixture of several various cultures.\r\n\r\nIndia gave birth to Hinduism, Buddhism, Jainism, Sikhism, and other religions. They are now collectively known as Indian religions. Today, Hinduism and Buddhism are the third and fourth-largest religions respectively of the world. Although India is a secular Hindu-majority country, it has a large Muslim population.\r\n\r\nFestivals\r\nIndia, being a multi-cultural, multi-ethnic and multi-religious society, celebrates holidays and festivals of various religions. Major festivals include Diwali, Durga puja, Holi, Ganesh puja, Navratri, Rath yatra, etc are there round the year.\r\n\r\nFood\r\nIndian food is a cosmopolitan cuisine that has so many ingredients. It is as diverse as India. Indian recipes use numerous ingredients, deploy a wide range of food preparation styles, cooking techniques, and culinary presentation. Thus the tastes of same food like salads, sauces, vegetables, meat, desserts vary from region to region.\r\n\r\nConclusion\r\nWe are proud of our cultural distinctiveness. We are proud to be the inhabitants of India. It is our duty to maintain its unique feature. We have to think beyond the petty interests and work for the broader goals of bringing prosperity and progress in society.','img/india.jpg','Chitti Vinay','2023-11-03 12:26:23'),(45,'Rajasthan','Rajasthan is the largest state of the Republic of India in terms of area . For the first time in 1800 AD, George Thomas named this province Rajputana. Famous historian James Tad named this state as Raithan or Rajasthan in \"Annals and Antiquities of Rajasthan\" [7] . This state has an international border of 1070 km with Pakistan , which is known as the Red Cliff Line, and a 4850 km inter-state border which is also connected to five other states of the country. In its south-west, Gujarat [8] , in the south-east Madhya Pradesh in the north, Punjab (India) in the north , Uttar Pradesh and Haryana in the north-east . The area of ​​the state is 3,42,239 square kilometers (132,140 square miles). According to 2011 census, the literacy rate of Rajasthan is 66.1%.\r\n\r\nThe capital of the state is Jaipur. Geographical features include the Thar Desert in the west and the end of the Ghaggar River. Aravalli range, which is prominent among the ancient ranges of the world, is the only mountain range of Rajasthan, which is a center of tourism, it includes Mount Abu and the world famous Delwara Temple . Three (four after the addition of Ramgarh Vishdhari) tiger reserves in Rajasthan.\r\n\r\nFamous places of Rajasthan\r\nJaipur\r\n\r\nHawa Mahal , Jaipur .\r\nJaipur [12] is famous for its grand forts, palaces and beautiful lakes, which attract tourists from all over the world.\r\nChandramahal (City Palace) was built by Maharaja Jai ​​Singh (II) and is a combination of Mughal and Rajasthani architecture.\r\nMaharaja Sawai Pratap Singh built Hawa Mahal in 1799 AD, whose architect was Lalchand Usta.\r\nAmer Fort has many building complexes including palaces, huge chambers, pillared galleries, gardens and temples.\r\nAmer Palace is an excellent example of the blend of Mughal and Hindu architectural styles.\r\nThe museum, named Albert Hall, was built by Sawai Ram Singh in 1876, on the arrival of the Prince of Wales to Jaipur, and opened to the public in 1886.\r\nThe Government Central Museum has a rich collection of ivory works, textiles, jewellery, carved wood works, miniatures, marble statues, arms and ammunitions.\r\nSawai Jai Singh (II) also built \' Sisodia Rani Ka Bagh \' for the residence of his Sisodia Rani.\r\nJal Mahal , a palace situated in the middle of Mansagar Lake , built for royal duck-hunting .\r\n\' Kanak Vrindavan \' is a popular temple complex in Jaipur famous for its ancient Govindeva idol.\r\nThe markets of Jaipur are vibrant and the shops are filled with colorful goods, which include handloom products, precious gems, textiles, enamel wares, Rajasthani paintings etc.\r\nJaipur is also famous for marble statues, blue pottery and Rajasthani juttis.\r\nThe major markets of Jaipur, from where you can buy some useful items, are Johri Bazaar, Bapu Bazaar, Nehru Bazaar, Chowra Rasta, Tripolia Bazaar and M.I. There are roads.\r\nRajasthan State Transport Corporation (RSRTC) has bus services to all the popular destinations of North India.\r\nIn Virat Nagar (old name Bairath) near Jaipur , where the Pandavas lived in exile, there is a unique temple called Vajrang Temple on the Panchkhand mountain, where the statue of Hanuman ji without a monkey\'s face and without a tail is installed, which was established by the immortal freedom fighter, Yashasvi. The author was Mahatma Ramchandra Veer .\r\nPanna Meena ki stepwell: The famous stepwell built during the reign of Sawai Jai Singh.\r\nBharatpur\r\nBharatpur , the \'Gate of Eastern Rajasthan\' , holds its importance in the tourism map of India .\r\nA major tourist destination in the present day map of India, Bharatpur has gone through several phases since the fifth century BCE.\r\nThe 18th century Ghana Bird Sanctuary , also known as Keoladeo Ghana National Park .\r\nAlso known as Lohagarh Iron Fort, Lohagarh is one of the major historical attractions of Bharatpur. which no one could conquer\r\nBharatpur Museum is a major source of insight into the heroic past of Rajasthan along with its royal glory.\r\nA beautiful garden, Nehru Park, is near the Bharatpur Museum.\r\nDeeg Jalmahal is an attractive palace, which was built by the Jat rulers of Bharatpur .\r\nJodhpur\r\nJodhpur, founded in 1459 by Rao Jodha, head of a dynasty known as the Rathores, is centrally located in the western part of Rajasthan, the state\'s second largest city, and a popular tourist destination with picturesque palaces, forts and temples. Is the destination.\r\nHandloom, textile industries and metal based industries contribute to the economy of the city.\r\nMehrangarh Fort , 125 meters high and spread over an area of ​​5 km, is one of the largest forts in India and houses many ornate palaces such as Moti Mahal , Phool Mahal , Sheesh Mahal . Inside the museum there is also a rich collection of miniatures, musical instruments, costumes, armory etc.\r\nThe Jodhpur state was a princely state in the Marwar region that lasted from 1250 to 1949. Its capital remained in Jodhpur city since 1950.\r\nSawai madhopur\r\nSawai Madhopur city was founded by the former Maharaja of Jaipur Sawai Madho Singh I in 1765 AD and Sawai Madhopur district was created in his name on May 15, 1949. This Meena dominated district has great historical importance.\r\nThe first national park of Rajasthan state is located in this district, which is known as Ranthambore National Park . Due to this garden, Sawai Madhopur is also known as \'Tiger City\' in Rajasthan.\r\nThe historic Ranthambore fort of Chauhan dynasty in Sawai Madhopur district is included in the world heritage, this fort is unique in the world due to its natural structure and impenetrable security. The most famous ruler of this fort, Maharaja Hammir Dev Chauhan, has been quite famous in the history of Rajasthan due to his stubbornness.\r\nThe painting of tigers at Sawaimadhopur railway station has a unique identity in the world, hence it can be called a wildlife friendly station.\r\nThe famous temple of Chauth Mata is located in Chauth Ka Barwada which was built during the reign of Jaipur King Bhim Singh.\r\nTemple of Lord Pisces  : A great temple built by Meena Samaj in Chauth Ka Barwada with a cost of Rs 7 crore.\r\nTwenty-four Bagavats are famous here and later Lord Devnarayan was born in this lineage.\r\nBundi\r\n\r\n1. This city was founded by Maharaja Bunda Meena.\r\n\r\n2. Jaita Sagar Lake: It was built by Jaita Meena, the ruler of Bundi.\r\n\r\nconstructed lake\r\n\r\nBarmer 1.Kiradu Temple 2.Juna 3.Viratra Mata Temple\r\n\r\n\r\n','img/rajasthan.jpg','Jitendra Choudhary','2023-11-03 12:32:00');
